                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 13, 1953, Lieutenant General <persName corresp="#p_RPG1">Gustavo Rojas
                        Pinilla</persName> launched a successful Army <hi rend="italic">coup
                        d’etat</hi> against the regime of President <persName corresp="#p_GL1"
                        >Laureano Gómez</persName>, which resulted in the deposition of <persName
                        corresp="#p_GL1">Gómez</persName> and his replacement by a military junta of
                    13 officers under the leadership of <persName corresp="#p_RPG1">Rojas
                        Pinilla</persName>. The progress of the coup and related political
                    developments were reported in despatch 990, from Bogotá, dated June 17, 1953,
                    not printed (721.00/6–1753). Additional pertinent documentation is in file
                    721.00 for 1953.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
